   <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>table<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n\n@functions <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n     <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Inject</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">IJSRuntime</span> JSRuntime <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">set</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">override</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">OnAfterRender</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>JSRuntime<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Ejs</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">EnableRipple</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Enable ripple for Switch label By default, label with ripple effect is not available in Switch. You can achieve this using  \nproperty. The…","fields":{"slug":"/switch/how-to/enable-ripple-for-switch-label/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/switch/how-to/enable-ripple-for-switch-label/","previous":{"html":"<h1 id=\"set-disabled-state\"><a href=\"#set-disabled-state\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Set disabled state</h1>\n<p>Switch can be disabled by setting the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents~Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents.Buttons.EjsSwitch~Disabled.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">disabled</code></a> property to true.</p>\n<p>The following example illustrates how to disable support in Switch component.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">Index.razor</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsSwitch</span> ID<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"default1\"</span> Disabled<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"true\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsSwitch<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>","id":"b5fa80a2-239b-5cef-90c7-7040c2c50fd8","fields":{"slug":"/switch/how-to/set-disabled-state/","parentPath":"switch/how-to","childPath":"set-disabled-state","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4","header":"","breadCrumb":"Switch/How To/Set disabled state","isReleaseNotes":false,"title":"How to Set disabled state in Blazor [Preview] Switch component - Syncfusion","description":"Checkout and learn about Set disabled state in Blazor [Preview] Switch component of Syncfusion Essential JS 2, and more details.","platform":"Blazor [Preview]","isRobots":true}},"next":{"html":"<h1 id=\"customize-the-appearance-of-a-switch\"><a href=\"#customize-the-appearance-of-a-switch\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize the appearance of a Switch</h1>\n<p>You can customize the appearance of the Switch component using the CSS rules. Define your own CSS rules according to your requirement and assign the class name to the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/cref_files/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents~Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents.Buttons.EjsSwitch~CssClass.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">cssClass</code></a> property.</p>\n<h2 id=\"customize-switch-bar-and-handle\"><a href=\"#customize-switch-bar-and-handle\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Customize Switch bar and handle</h2>\n<p>Switch bar and handle can be customized as per requirement using CSS rules. Switch bar and handle customized using <code class=\"language-text\">cssClass</code> property. In the following sample, the <code class=\"language-text\">border-radius</code> CSS property for <code class=\"language-text\">e-switch-inner</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">e-switch-handle</code> elements was changed border radius circle to square shape.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">Index.razor</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>ul<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsSwitch</span> ID<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"switch11\"</span> CssClass<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"square\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsSwitch<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsSwitch</span> ID<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"switch22\"</span> CssClass<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"custom-switch\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsSwitch<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n            <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">EjsSwitch</span> ID<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"switch3\"</span> CssClass<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"handle-text\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>EjsSwitch<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>li<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>ul<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>  <code class=\"language-text\">_Host.cshtml</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token style\"><span class=\"token language-css\">\n <span class=\"token comment\">/* Square Switch */</span>\n <span class=\"token selector\">.e-switch-wrapper.square .e-switch-inner,\n .e-switch-wrapper.square .e-switch-handle</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n     <span class=\"token property\">border-radius</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n <span class=\"token selector\">li</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n     <span class=\"token property\">list-style</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> none<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n     <span class=\"token property\">pa